La variabile <var>CONFIG_PROTECT</var> contiene una lista (i cui elementi sono separati da spazi) di directory dove Portage non sovrascriverà nessun file "alla cieca", ma tratterà questi come configurazioni, permettendo all'utente di controllare manualmente se le modifiche siano necessarie e valide oppure no. Le sottodirectories delle directories elencate possono essere escluse tramite la variabile <var>CONFIG_PROTECT_MASK</var>.

The variable has a sane default setting handled by the Portage installation and the users' Gentoo [[Profile (Portage)|profile]]. It can be extended through the system environment (which is often used by applications that update the variable through their {{Path|/etc/env.d}} file) and the users' {{Path|[[:/etc/portage/make.conf]]}} setting.

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/portage/make.conf|title=Example CONFIG_PROTECT use in make.conf|lang=bash|1=
CONFIG_PROTECT="/var/bind"
}}

See also the [[Handbook:AMD64/Working/EnvVar|Environment variables]] chapter in the Gentoo Handbook.<noinclude>[[Category:Portage]]</noinclude>
